      "content": "i was looking at old photos today and i didnt even recognize the person in them. it feels like that person died a long time ago and i'm just... i'm just the leftover parts. like i'm just walking around as a ghost of who i was supposed to be. it’s just so exhausting to keep pretending there’s actually someone still in here.",
